message.content: Based on the process list extracted from the memory image, the "AcroRd32.exe" process (PID 1752) is the most likely responsible for the initial exploit. AcroRd32.exe is associated with Adobe Acrobat Reader, which is commonly used to open PDF files. Since the incident involved an email pointing to a PDF file, it is plausible that the exploit originated from this process when the employee opened the PDF file. Further analysis of this process and its memory space would be crucial to determine the exact nature of the exploit and any malicious activities it may have initiated.
